1
00:01:52,430 --> 00:01:57,260
So far, one player has been eliminated
from the Upper Yard survival game,

2
00:01:57,260 --> 00:01:59,350
and eighty remain.

3
00:02:00,560 --> 00:02:04,060
They must have lacked
God's divine protection...

4
00:02:07,070 --> 00:02:11,030
Meanwhile, four of the Straw Hats
set out to search for gold.

5
00:02:11,530 --> 00:02:16,530
Their goal: the treasure resting
within the ruins of an ancient city.

6
00:02:17,530 --> 00:02:21,160
They head directly south
from the sacrificial altar.

7
00:02:22,620 --> 00:02:24,710
Directly...

8
00:02:25,330 --> 00:02:27,130
south...

9
00:02:34,760 --> 00:02:37,760
The forest sure has become lively.

10
00:02:38,260 --> 00:02:40,810
This house is far away from the city,

11
00:02:41,430 --> 00:02:43,730
so naturally the forest has engulfed it.

12
00:02:43,730 --> 00:02:47,650
I wonder if the ruins of the actual
city are in better condition...

13
00:02:54,530 --> 00:02:56,280
Woman!

14
00:02:56,280 --> 00:02:59,780
This route leads to God's Shrine!

15
00:02:59,780 --> 00:03:02,290
To go any farther would be saacrilege!

16
00:03:04,410 --> 00:03:05,960
Get down from there!

17
00:03:06,250 --> 00:03:11,710
What's sacrilege is that you don't even
realize the historical value of these ruins!

18
00:03:12,300 --> 00:03:13,920
How impudent!

19
00:03:14,260 --> 00:03:15,720
Do you have business with me?

20
00:03:15,720 --> 00:03:16,880
What do you want?

21
00:03:18,180 --> 00:03:21,100
Simple! By God's maandate,

22
00:03:21,100 --> 00:03:23,810
I'm to chop the Shandians
and you Blue Sea people

23
00:03:23,810 --> 00:03:27,020
into pieces with this aaxe dial!

24
00:03:29,860 --> 00:03:31,400
Seis Fleurs!

25
00:03:33,780 --> 00:03:34,990
Twist!

26
00:03:42,080 --> 00:03:44,200
How barbaric.

27
00:03:48,620 --> 00:03:51,340
G-Get me out of here!

28
00:03:51,340 --> 00:03:53,090
No way!

29
00:03:53,090 --> 00:03:55,630
Stop following! Let me go!

30
00:04:15,900 --> 00:04:16,860
Shandians!

31
00:04:17,860 --> 00:04:19,360
Warrior monks!

32
00:04:40,680 --> 00:04:41,640
I...

33
00:04:43,350 --> 00:04:46,350
I never should've come here!

34
00:04:55,530 --> 00:04:57,610
That'll teach you, warrior monk!

35
00:05:00,280 --> 00:05:02,620
Many of our allies have fallen!

36
00:05:02,620 --> 00:05:03,780
Damn!

37
00:05:03,780 --> 00:05:06,620
These warrior monks are troublesome!

38
00:05:06,620 --> 00:05:09,580
Right. Right. Right...

39
00:05:09,580 --> 00:05:12,330
Is that one of the Blue Sea
people Wyper mentioned?!

40
00:05:12,710 --> 00:05:14,340
He must be eliminated!

41
00:05:18,170 --> 00:05:19,170
A guerrilla!

42
00:05:20,720 --> 00:05:22,260
Guess he wants a fight!

43
00:05:23,090 --> 00:05:24,430
Die!

44
00:05:24,760 --> 00:05:27,390
I'm not sure what this is about, but...!

45
00:05:32,850 --> 00:05:35,400
What the hell is with you guys?!

46
00:05:38,900 --> 00:05:41,280
Please, forgive me! I give up!

47
00:05:41,650 --> 00:05:43,280
I give up!

48
00:05:43,280 --> 00:05:44,660
I lose!

49
00:05:44,660 --> 00:05:46,780
Please spaare me...!

50
00:05:51,500 --> 00:05:52,920
Another one?!

51
00:05:53,290 --> 00:05:54,290
Hey, you!

52
00:05:54,290 --> 00:05:57,340
If you're not a priest,
then don't attack me!

53
00:05:57,340 --> 00:05:59,460
I don't have time for this!

54
00:06:23,070 --> 00:06:24,910
Bastard!

55
00:06:24,910 --> 00:06:27,280
What the hell are those
flashing pistols?!

56
00:06:29,830 --> 00:06:30,870
Where'd he go?!

57
00:06:50,680 --> 00:06:52,680
You're pretty tough.

58
00:06:52,680 --> 00:06:55,650
I apologize. I underestimated you,
Blue Sea person.

59
00:07:01,440 --> 00:07:04,650
No. I should apologize.

60
00:07:05,400 --> 00:07:07,570
I was sure you were just some lackey.

61
00:07:22,840 --> 00:07:24,510
He didn't even move his feet!

62
00:07:30,220 --> 00:07:33,220
They said there's all kinds of wavers...

63
00:07:34,180 --> 00:07:37,190
Are those skate things
just another type?

64
00:07:39,110 --> 00:07:41,440
He's using blasts to propel himself!

65
00:07:42,150 --> 00:07:43,320
And...

66
00:07:43,320 --> 00:07:45,780
his pistols flash with each shot!

67
00:07:46,240 --> 00:07:49,070
Thanks to those, I can't
keep my eyes on him!

68
00:07:50,490 --> 00:07:52,120
Where'd he go?!

69
00:07:57,830 --> 00:07:58,670
Tiger...

70
00:07:58,670 --> 00:08:00,040
Three swords?!

71
00:08:00,040 --> 00:08:01,340
...Trap!

72
00:08:05,880 --> 00:08:07,840
Bastard!

73
00:08:20,190 --> 00:08:24,030
A Blue Sea swordsman who can't
even use wavers or dials...

74
00:08:24,480 --> 00:08:26,570
You don't stand a chance!

75
00:08:28,820 --> 00:08:31,530
Know what this is?!

76
00:08:31,910 --> 00:08:32,990
What the...?!

77
00:08:33,700 --> 00:08:35,120
Milky Dial!

78
00:08:40,210 --> 00:08:44,500
Aerial combat isn't just
jumping around desperately!

79
00:08:46,590 --> 00:08:48,590
A-An eel?!

80
00:08:59,810 --> 00:09:03,400
This would probably
be pretty good broiled...

81
00:09:23,830 --> 00:09:26,340
I-I really screwed up!

82
00:09:26,340 --> 00:09:28,340
Am I an idiot?!

83
00:09:29,130 --> 00:09:33,340
As if I wasn't struggling enough
to keep up with this bastard...

84
00:09:34,470 --> 00:09:35,970
then I get shot in the leg!

85
00:09:36,350 --> 00:09:40,810
What can I do about
those blinding pistols?!

86
00:09:41,480 --> 00:09:42,440
That's it!

87
00:09:43,270 --> 00:09:45,980
Those are some fancy
weapons you got there!

88
00:09:49,440 --> 00:09:51,320
But too bad!

89
00:09:51,320 --> 00:09:53,450
Look! I have goggles!

90
00:09:53,780 --> 00:09:58,200
Your flashing pistols
won't work on me anymore!

91
00:09:58,950 --> 00:10:01,040
So there's no point continuing.

92
00:10:01,040 --> 00:10:03,750
They don't look
like sunglasses to me...

93
00:10:04,210 --> 00:10:05,750
He saw through it!

94
00:10:06,090 --> 00:10:09,130
You don't seem fond
of my flash guns.

95
00:10:09,550 --> 00:10:11,380
Close combat is vital to swordsmen.

96
00:10:11,380 --> 00:10:13,930
You're no match for me.

97
00:10:14,760 --> 00:10:18,970
I don't know what
you guys came for...

98
00:10:19,430 --> 00:10:25,560
but you're our enemy
as long as you stay here.

99
00:10:25,980 --> 00:10:28,270
Now die already!

100
00:10:28,270 --> 00:10:30,360
That injury looks painful, after all.

101
00:10:30,860 --> 00:10:32,530
Spare me your sympathies.

102
00:10:32,530 --> 00:10:34,200
You only grazed my leg.

103
00:10:35,610 --> 00:10:41,370
Getting distracted by food
proves that I still lack resolve.

104
00:10:42,250 --> 00:10:46,880
Here's the perfect situation
to try out that technique...

105
00:10:47,750 --> 00:10:49,300
Shall I give it a shot?

106
00:11:11,360 --> 00:11:12,820
Running away?

107
00:11:14,610 --> 00:11:19,870
Eyes, ears, nose,
tongue, body, mind...

108
00:11:19,870 --> 00:11:24,370
These are the six roots of man
that hold good, evil, and peace.

109
00:11:24,710 --> 00:11:26,120
What are you talking about?

110
00:11:27,120 --> 00:11:30,130
And each of those is
either pure or impure.

111
00:11:30,790 --> 00:11:33,090
Thirty-six worldly
desires in a lifetime...

112
00:11:36,670 --> 00:11:40,350
I now have the barrel
of a cannon pointed at you.

113
00:11:40,350 --> 00:11:43,390
Your pistols versus my cannon...

114
00:11:43,390 --> 00:11:46,560
In both range and power,
my weapon is superior.

115
00:11:47,020 --> 00:11:48,600
You've done well so far...

116
00:11:49,560 --> 00:11:50,610
but it ends here!

117
00:11:56,860 --> 00:11:58,280
A cannon?

118
00:11:58,660 --> 00:12:00,030
Have you gone mad?

119
00:12:00,030 --> 00:12:02,240
Where is this weapon of yours?!

120
00:12:03,370 --> 00:12:05,500
Have you ever seen...

121
00:12:05,500 --> 00:12:07,210
a flying slash?

122
00:12:07,210 --> 00:12:09,120
Nonsense!

123
00:12:11,090 --> 00:12:12,710
One-Sword Style:

124
00:12:19,390 --> 00:12:23,430
Thirty-Six-Pound Phoenix!

125
00:12:40,660 --> 00:12:42,120
Sorry.

126
00:12:43,200 --> 00:12:46,330
Nothing personal...

127
00:12:46,330 --> 00:12:50,330
but you can't tell me
when to give up and die.

128
00:12:53,380 --> 00:12:56,340
I'll do whatever it takes to survive.

129
00:13:21,950 --> 00:13:24,620
Darn it...

130
00:13:26,580 --> 00:13:30,210
I'm completely lost...

131
00:13:30,210 --> 00:13:32,540
Guys!

132
00:13:32,540 --> 00:13:35,790
Luffy! Zoro! Robin!

133
00:13:37,170 --> 00:13:40,420
Am I going to be left here to die?

134
00:13:40,420 --> 00:13:43,300
Do reindeer go to heaven?

135
00:13:43,300 --> 00:13:45,930
Will the doctor be waiting for me?

136
00:13:48,180 --> 00:13:50,810
No, I can't think like that!

137
00:13:50,810 --> 00:13:52,390
I'm a doctor!

138
00:13:52,390 --> 00:13:56,020
I can't think about death so casually!

139
00:13:58,030 --> 00:14:00,530
But I wonder what heaven is like...

140
00:14:01,700 --> 00:14:04,030
Wait, isn't this heaven?

141
00:14:04,030 --> 00:14:04,820
Huh?!

142
00:14:06,830 --> 00:14:09,790
I'm surrounded by ruins
all of a sudden.

143
00:14:10,790 --> 00:14:12,290
Maybe everyone made it here!

144
00:14:12,290 --> 00:14:14,920
I guess I really am great!

145
00:14:14,920 --> 00:14:17,040
Oh! Could I be the first one here?!

146
00:14:17,040 --> 00:14:17,920
Yeah!

147
00:14:17,920 --> 00:14:20,010
My nose must've helped!

148
00:14:20,010 --> 00:14:24,090
Yay! I'm the first!

149
00:14:26,100 --> 00:14:27,430
A tanuki...

150
00:14:40,360 --> 00:14:42,950
Shoot me all you want, it's no use!

151
00:14:42,950 --> 00:14:46,820
Cannons and guns won't work on me!

152
00:14:46,820 --> 00:14:48,240
Apparently not.

153
00:14:49,080 --> 00:14:51,580
Let's try a different approach.

154
00:15:02,800 --> 00:15:03,970
What's this smell?!

155
00:15:03,970 --> 00:15:06,800
This weapon is known
as a burn bazooka,

156
00:15:06,800 --> 00:15:10,390
which houses a breath dial
filled with gas.

157
00:15:10,390 --> 00:15:15,980
The expelled gas ignites into
blue flames that burn prey to a crisp!

158
00:15:33,330 --> 00:15:34,330
What the...?!

159
00:15:34,330 --> 00:15:36,170
It blasted through that huge tree!

160
00:15:37,540 --> 00:15:38,290
Huh?

161
00:15:39,040 --> 00:15:40,090
He's gone!

162
00:15:50,640 --> 00:15:52,510
Gum-Gum...

163
00:15:53,310 --> 00:15:54,810
Pistol!

164
00:16:02,190 --> 00:16:05,030
Gum-Gum Stamp!

165
00:16:27,380 --> 00:16:28,550
That was close!

166
00:16:29,550 --> 00:16:31,760
Gum-Gum...

167
00:16:32,600 --> 00:16:33,720
Spear!

168
00:16:51,740 --> 00:16:53,370
If it's a bazooka you want,

169
00:16:53,870 --> 00:16:55,490
it's a bazooka you'll get!

170
00:16:55,490 --> 00:16:57,290
Straw Hat!

171
00:16:57,790 --> 00:16:59,750
Gum-Gum...

172
00:16:59,750 --> 00:17:01,420
Burn...

173
00:17:05,500 --> 00:17:08,630
– ...Bazooka!
– ...Bazooka!

174
00:17:26,530 --> 00:17:28,990
Straw Hat!

175
00:17:33,910 --> 00:17:36,240
That bastard!

176
00:17:40,160 --> 00:17:41,670
Sanji!

177
00:17:44,080 --> 00:17:46,460
Sanji!

178
00:17:48,710 --> 00:17:50,670
Sanji!

179
00:17:54,300 --> 00:17:55,510
– Sanji!
– H-Hey!

180
00:17:56,260 --> 00:17:58,520
Say something, Sanji!

181
00:18:00,980 --> 00:18:02,190
Hey!

182
00:18:02,640 --> 00:18:04,650
What's going on?!

183
00:18:04,650 --> 00:18:05,940
Sanji!

184
00:18:12,530 --> 00:18:15,120
Hey! I don't hear a heartbeat!

185
00:18:15,120 --> 00:18:16,330
No way!

186
00:18:22,580 --> 00:18:24,670
What a foolish man.

187
00:18:24,670 --> 00:18:29,960
And I didn't even come
bearing malice.

188
00:18:31,300 --> 00:18:34,300
Then why are you here?!

189
00:18:36,010 --> 00:18:38,720
Such a cold-hearted greeting...

190
00:18:42,230 --> 00:18:47,900
It's truly been six long years,
former god Gan Fall...

